# Caddyfile
#
# NOTE (Phase 1 security fix — C6):
# The previous `:81` block accepted an arbitrary `XTransformPort` query
# parameter and proxied to `localhost:{port}`. This was an open SSRF vector
# (e.g. an attacker could reach internal services on any localhost port).
# That block has been removed. The app is served directly on :3000 by Next.js;
# Caddy is not used as a proxy in front of it in this configuration.
#
# If you need a public-facing reverse proxy in the future, configure it
# explicitly with a hardcoded upstream and never allow caller-controlled
# port selection.
